1.title: Volcano to the Seas

episode of.title: It's How You Get There (TV Series 2017– )

1.plot: Greg White and Julian Taylor compare a 2016 Mustang 5.0, modified by Richard Petty's Garage, to a classic 1969 Chevy Camaro in a scenic race to the Sierra Nevada Brewery in Asheville, N.C.

2.title: Down and Dirty

episode of.title: It's How You Get There (TV Series 2017– )

2.plot: Greg gets a 557-horsepower Rocky Ridge Alpine-edition Silverado and Julian gets a 435-horsepower Jeep Wrangler before they head to Richard Petty's personal farm to race the newly acquired vehicles in the mud.

3.title: West Virginia is for Fun

episode of.title: It's How You Get There (TV Series 2017– )

3.plot: The boys are joined in West Virginia by Jenn Barlow as they run a timed race in a Porsche SUV on Snowshoe Mountain, tear through the woods of Bear Wallow Trailhead in Mahindra UTVs, and ride to New River Gorge on two Harley-Davidson motorcycles.

4.title: Moab Madness

episode of.title: It's How You Get There (TV Series 2017– )

4.plot: Greg, Julian and Jenn take on the Top of the World Trail in Moab, Utah, where they test the mettle of three rock-ready Jeep Rubicons and try not to get stuck on the way to the top.

5.title: Road Trip

episode of.title: It's How You Get There (TV Series 2017– )

5.plot: Greg takes Julian out on Lake Michigan in an extremely versatile boat with a big, road-ready surprise; Julian is introduced to the RV lifestyle; Julian and Greg circuit race two jacked-up go-carts and drag race two high-powered riding mowers.

6.title: Horsepower Raceway

episode of.title: It's How You Get There (TV Series 2017– )

6.plot: Greg and Julian head to Chuckwalla Valley Raceway in Desert City, Calif.; they test out two motorcycles, a Ducati 959 Panigale and a Suzuki GSXR-1000, then they switch to a 2016 Dodge Viper ACR and a Challenger Hellcat SRT.
